abstract: U.S. officials have told Democratic presidential contender Bernie Sanders that Russia is trying to help his campaign, the Washington Post reported on Friday.
snippet: U.S. officials have told Democratic presidential contender Bernie Sanders that Russia is trying to help his campaign, the Washington Post reported on Friday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. officials have told Democratic presidential contender Bernie Sanders that Russia is trying to help his campaign, the Washington Post reported on Friday.
headline_main: U.S. Officials Tell Democrat Sanders Russia Is Trying to Help His Campaign: Washington Post
headline_print_headline: U.S. Officials Tell Democrat Sanders Russia Is Trying to Help His Campaign: Washington Post

abstract: President Donald Trump rallied supporters in the battleground state of Nevada on the eve of the state's caucuses and predicted chaos once again for Democrats for their management of the voting process,
snippet: President Donald Trump rallied supporters in the battleground state of Nevada on the eve of the state's caucuses and predicted chaos once again for Democrats for their management of the voting process,
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — President Donald Trump rallied supporters in the battleground state of Nevada on the eve of the state's caucuses and predicted chaos once again for Democrats for their management of the voting process,
headline_main: Trump Rallies Nevada GOP Ahead of State's Dem Caucuses
headline_print_headline: Trump Rallies Nevada GOP Ahead of State's Dem Caucuses

abstract: The new acting director of national intelligence also asked to see the facts underlying the finding that Russia is interfering in the 2020 election and favors President Trump’s re-election.
snippet: The new acting director of national intelligence also asked to see the facts underlying the finding that Russia is interfering in the 2020 election and favors President Trump’s re-election.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Richard Grenell’s tenure as the nation’s top intelligence official may be short-lived, but he wasted no time this week starting to shape his team of advisers, ousting his office’s No. 2 official — a longtime intelligence officer — and bringing in an expert on Trump conspiracy theories to help lead the agency, according to officials.

abstract: In questions before a grand jury, prosecutors have focused on whether a top pilot misled regulators about new flight control software in the 737 Max plane.
snippet: In questions before a grand jury, prosecutors have focused on whether a top pilot misled regulators about new flight control software in the 737 Max plane.
lead_paragraph: Federal prosecutors investigating Boeing are examining whether the company knowingly misled the Federal Aviation Administration while it was seeking the regulator’s approval for its 737 Max plane, according to two people familiar with the matter who spoke on the condition of anonymity to discuss an active inquiry.

abstract: Arizona Gov. Doug Ducey spent much of his first term working to repair the damage to the state's reputation caused by a 2010 tough-on-immigrants law known as SB 1070 that his predecessor signed.

lead_paragraph: PHOENIX — Arizona Gov. Doug Ducey spent much of his first term working to repair the damage to the state's reputation caused by a 2010 tough-on-immigrants law known as SB 1070 that his predecessor signed.
headline_main: Arizona Governor Pulls Immigration Plan Amid Business Revolt

abstract: As a diverse crowd filled a college student union this week, they swapped stories of seeking refuge in the U.S. or living in households that were a mix of U.S. citizens and people in the country illegally. They hoped to share their experiences with presidential candidates seeking support ahead of Saturday's Nevada caucuses.
snippet: As a diverse crowd filled a college student union this week, they swapped stories of seeking refuge in the U.S. or living in households that were a mix of U.S. citizens and people in the country illegally. They hoped to share their experiences wit...
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — As a diverse crowd filled a college student union this week, they swapped stories of seeking refuge in the U.S. or living in households that were a mix of U.S. citizens and people in the country illegally. They hoped to share their experiences with presidential candidates seeking support ahead of Saturday's Nevada caucuses.
headline_main: Democrats Avoid Immigration Specifics Ahead of Nevada Vote
headline_print_headline: Democrats Avoid Immigration Specifics Ahead of Nevada Vote

abstract: Trump administration officials on Friday acknowledged that U.S. President Donald Trump's visit to India next week will not result in even a limited trade deal, saying they still have major concerns over India's trade barriers.
snippet: Trump administration officials on Friday acknowledged that U.S. President Donald Trump's visit to India next week will not result in even a limited trade deal, saying they still have major concerns over India's trade barriers.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Trump administration officials on Friday acknowledged that U.S. President Donald Trump's visit to India next week will not result in even a limited trade deal, saying they still have major concerns over India's trade barriers.
headline_main: U.S., India at Odds Over Trade as Trump Heads for Encounter With Modi: U.S. Officials
headline_print_headline: U.S., India at Odds Over Trade as Trump Heads for Encounter With Modi: U.S. Officials

abstract: The museum has released emails about its decision to blur some signs in a photo of the 2017 Women’s March that were critical of President Trump.
snippet: The museum has released emails about its decision to blur some signs in a photo of the 2017 Women’s March that were critical of President Trump.
lead_paragraph: It did not take long for conspiracy theories and accusations of censorship to emerge after the National Archives and Records Administration admitted it had altered a photo of the 2017 Women’s March to hide disparaging references to President Trump.
